channel.title: APISENSE® Documentation
channel.description: APISENSE® leverages data collected from a crowd of mobile devices. Observe and innovate using users' feedback, in real time!

item.title: Version 1.11.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Honeycomb: Add an home page with current Honeycomb version.
    • Honeycomb: Add modular backends support (see here how to configure them). You can choose between:
      • MongoDB
      • InfluxDB
      • Neo4J
    • Android:Sdk: New stings available:
      • Crypto,
      • DBHelper,
      • Notification,
    • Android:Sdk: Add the possibility to run APISENSE as a foreground service.
  • Enhancements:
    • Dashboard: You can’t delete a Honeycomb used by crops anymore. You will have to remove every crops using it before.
    • Android:Sdk: The time converter now handle milliseconds Have fun!

item.title: Version 1.10.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Honeycomb: Add a manageable per user quota to avoid a scientist pushing too much data.
    • Dashboard: See your quotas status and manage your backends quota settings.
    • Android:Sdk: New stings available:
      • Cpu,
      • Memory,
      • Rotation,
      • Gravity,
      • Gyroscope,
      • Accelerometer,
      • Proximity,
      • Pressure,
      • Light,
      • Visualization.
  • Enhancements:
    • Android:SDK: Wifi Sting now returns the right value for authentication() method.
    • Dashboard: Fix some errors when a backend server is not available.
    • Android:SDK: Check Sting availability on initialization to avoid using not-working ones.

Have fun!

item.title: Version 1.9.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Android:Sdk: You do not need to create a Bee with a custom app anymore. See the SDK Documentation.
    • Android:Sdk: New stings available:
      • Call,
      • Device,
      • Local Storage,
      • Network Analysis,
      • System,
  • Enhancements:
    • Android:SDK: Improvement in the reported exceptions details.
    • Android:SDK: The SDK is now modular, you will have to import sting packages

Please note that the core package of the Android SDK changed from com.apisense to io.apisense.

Have fun!

item.title: Version 1.8.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Android:Bee: Create a bee account from your Facebook or Google account.
    • Android:SDK: New methods to stop all the crops.
  • Enhancements:
    • Dashboard: New script management, you can now backup scripts for reuse.
    • Dashboard: User creation does not require invitations anymore.
    • Honeycomb: Docker image is lighter, using openjdk:1.8-jre.
    • Android:Sdk: APISENSE® SDK is now available from Maven central.
    • Android:Sdk: User creation now requires an email validation (if not created via a social login).
    • Android:Sdk: Every Bee can change its password.
    • Android:Sdk: Capture period can be changed on location sting.
    • Android:Sdk: Stings skeletons are now fully generated.

Have fun!

item.title: Version 1.7.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Dashboard: Separation between the Dashboard (available from https://apisense.io) and the Honeycomb (data endpoint). You can now manage your own Honeycomb server and use it as backend for any of your crops. Or, you can adopt to the official Honeycomb server.
    • Dashboard: Add the possibility to see reported exceptions about your deployed crops. Exceptions will be reported from Android SDK 1.7.1
    • [1.7.1] Dashboard: You can now clear data from a crop
  • Enhancements:
    • Android:Bee: Graphic enhancement of the whole Android app.
    • Android:Bee: Application is available for Android N.
    • Android:SDK: location sting now retrieve current position in Android system for each call on data accessors.
  • Fixed bugs:
    • Android:SDK: APISENSE® does not define its own file provider anymore for the Form sting,
    • [1.7.1] Dashboard: The “Download all” zip is now correctly generated. which was mixing authorities for multiple applications using the SDK.
    • Android:SDK: Resolved crash with GCM and any application using android N.
    • Android:SDK: Runtime exception on script will not crash the applications anymore.

Have fun!

item.title: Version 1.6.0 is available!
item.description:
• Features:
    • Hive service API is internationalized, and now provides error codes.
    • You can now start and disable your crop remotely for mobile apps linked to GCM.
  • Enhancements:
    • Graphic enhancement of the whole server interface.
    • Deploying a script automatically enables the associated crop.
    • Hive no longer have info about uploaded data size.
  • Fixed bugs:
    • Mobile apps name are limited to 40 characters.
    • Read only API key is now selectable on Firefox.
    • Commented stings in script will no longer appear on used stings.
    • Stings will not be duplicated in used stings.
    • Android (Wifi Sting): SSID will not be between escaped quotes anymore.
    • Android (CropManager): synchronise method will subscribe to crops GCM channel.
    • Android: Crop update will not multiply records anymore.

Have fun!

item.title: Here comes 1.5.0 !
item.description:
• Features:
    • The SDK now needs an initialization key to contact the Hive, See there.
    • You can now upload media (video, audio, and pictures) from form.
    • Needed runtime permissions for Android M are now declared per Sting, you can see required and missing runtime permissions for each crop.
    • You can write scripts to process each uploaded data block before insertion in database. More info over here.
  • Enhancements:
    • The SDK will now automatically log out users whose session has become invalid.
    • The Honeycomb UI has been refactored, hope you like it better.
IMPORTANT: If you created your own application using APISENSE, you must authorize your SDK or it will not work anymore.

Enjoy!

item.title: 1.4.0 available !
item.description:
More more more !

  • You can now install a crop using its QRCode
  • More control on your crop, public, private and now… Unlisted ! Everybody can use the crop, but only with the right QRCode (or ID)!
  • The script editor has also been enhanced, now giving autocompletion and automatically binding you to the documentation of the stings you use.
  • You can add your custom stings to the editor autocompletion.
  • Last but not least, the servers now uses HTTPS to communicate!

Have fun!

item.title: Wait, there is more! 1.3.0 available !
item.description:
We bring you this new version with some nice new features!

  • Google Cloud Messaging: Link your application to the Google notification service to automatically update your collect on deployement. Over here to see how to do it!
  • New Sting: the form: Create your form to ask questions to the user.
  • Filter your collected data before using them: You want to save some bandwidth or lower your treatment on custom views? Create a filter to make your data what you want them to be.

Have fun!

item.title: Big update ! 1.2.0 available !
item.description:
After a little bit more than two months of work we are glad to share with you our new SDK version ! With it comes a lot of new features, check-it out:

  • Privacy managment: You can setup your privacy settings to only run collects that use things you want to share and automatically stop the others.
  • Google play games: Let’s have some fun, unlock some nice achievements and see your progression!
  • Collect statistics: See how many people are contributing to every collect, always good to know you’re not alone! (but you can be the first :D)

Hope you like it!
